      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 24.1</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 24.1</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>企者不立，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>He who stands on his tiptoes does not stand firm; he who stretches his legs does not walk (easily).</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-024__align-002">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-024</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 24.2</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 24.2</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>跨者不行，自見者不明，自是者不彰，自伐者無功，自矜者不長。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>(So), he who displays himself does not shine; he who asserts his own views is not distinguished; he who vaunts himself does not find his merit acknowledged; he who is self- conceited has no superiority allowed to him.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-024__align-003">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-024</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 24.3</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 24.3</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>其在道也，曰餘食贅行。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Such conditions, viewed from the standpoint of the Dao, are like remnants of food, or a tumour on the body, which all dislike.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
